Recommended Measure(s) to Resolve Issue(: Reseed and monitor grass growth and bank stability in 2011.

Environmental Issue(s): HSoils - Water Erosion Vegetation – Weeds Water Quality and Quantity espeler Creek
Mitigative Measures Implemented During C: Appropriate vehicle crossing installed. Isolation method used. Fish salvage conducted. Reshaped the sunken banks of the crossing and compacted bed and banks. Wood cribbing was placed on the east side of the crossing to help in restoring the bank to original configuration while preventing siltation entering the watercourse. Installed Curlex and silt fence at restored banks. Hand picked, bagged and removed scentless chamomile (2 plants of noxious weed) from the construction right-of-way.
Outstanding Issue(s) from As-Built Repor: Potential for erosion/sedimentation until vegetation is established and for alteration of drainage patterns. Potential for weed introduction and spread.
Observations in 2010: Moderate density of green foxtail, field dock, creeping (Canada) thistle, foxtail barley and perennial sow-thistle on southeast bank. No erosion issues observed on right-of-way.
Recommended Measure(s) to Resolve Issue(: Follow weed control plan and monitor in 2011.

Mitigative Measures Implemented During C: Very soft slightly heaved spot on the construction right-of-way was noted in the area of the tie-in. This is directly related to the ditch/bellhole not being completely drained of water prior to backfill. 450 Dozer repacked exposed clay soils and replaced with topsoil lift. This area was flagged off to ensure no farming equipment will drive onto this soft area and it will be given a chance to naturally subside.
Outstanding Issue(s) from As-Built Repor: Potential admixing and alteration of drainage patterns due to either subsidence or heaving of trench line.
Observations in 2010: Moderate admixing on right-of-way.
Recommended Measure(s) to Resolve Issue(: Monitor crop growth in 2011. Source and add clean topsoil to address admixing in 2011, if warranted.

Observations in 2010: Moderate compaction observed on right-of-way during ground reconnaissance.
Recommended Measure(s) to Resolve Issue(: Monitor crop growth in 2011. Alleviate compaction, if warranted.

Observations in 2010: High density lamb’s-quarters, kochia, spear-leaved goosefoot, creeping (Canada) thistle, perennial sow-thistle, Russian thistle, redroot pigweed and prostrate pigweed observed on right-of-way during ground reconnaissance.
Recommended Measure(s) to Resolve Issue(: Follow weed control plan and monitor in 2011.

Environmental Issue(s): Vegetation – Weeds Land and Resource Use - Side-roll Irrigated Land, Drain Tile
Mitigative Measures Implemented During C: Weeds observed on topsoil piles on organic farm. Mechanical weed control on topsoil piles. Avoided peak irrigation season. Equipment cleaned prior to entry. Signs installed. No refuelling or waste receptacles installed. No herbicides to control weeds. Preconstruction surveyed construction right-of-way profile prepared. Drain tile locations were determined and a depth survey was conducted. Backfilling around the drain tiles occurred in lifts and each lift was compacted. Moved topsoil pile in spring 2009 where pivot irrigation is present to provide access for irrigation wheels. Prepared surveyed construction right-of-way profile of the reclaimed land. Compressed air/shovel cleaning of equipment prior to entry onto the Organic farm (Kroeker Farms) NE 11-2-4 WPM.
Outstanding Issue(s) from As-Built Repor: Potential for weed introduction and spread. Potential for drainage patterns to change.
Observations in 2010: No issues observed on right-of-way.
